<h2>4.1 Creating and Restoring a Backup</h2>
	<p>To create a backup of the current course, use the <em>Create</em> link found from the Backups page. All created backups are securely stored remotely on the ATutor. Created backups do not count towards the course's Max Course Size quota. Once the backup is created it will be listed on the main Backups page, where it can be managed.</p>

	<p>Once a backup has been created, you can restore it by selecting the backup and using the <kbd>Restore</kbd> button. The restoration process will given options for what material you want restored.</p>
